HEADWORD: outward-developing
<hw>outward-developing</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <fld>(Botany)</fld>
<def>Developing away from an axis, as in a flower cluster in which the
oldest flowers are in the center, the youngest near the edge.</def>⟦br⟧
